column5: Just to get some of you guys pumped up.This was my first walleye last opener on Cedar.Beautifull sunny coolish morning start.2-6 ft deep and a area about 100 ft. wide.About a fish on every cast.
Won't be long John, Ice just went off the local lakes here.
Thinking a month here.Oh well.About normal.I have some fantastic shore spots for walleyes and we soak off shore for lake trout.Not to many dull moments here
